Sentencas: Composites formed by the infiltration of 40 wt% La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-delta (LSSM) oxides (x = 0.1, 0.2, 0.3) into 65% porous yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) are investigated as anode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells for hydrocarbon oxidation.
Titulo: Assessment of perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-δ oxides as anodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: The oxygen non-stoichiometry and electrical conductivity of each LSSM-YSZ composite are determined by coulometric titration.
Titulo: Assessment of perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-δ oxides as anodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: As the concentration of Sc increases, the composites show higher phase stability and the electrical conductivity of LSSM is significantly affected by the Sc doping, the non-stoichiometric oxygen content, and oxygen partial pressure (p(O-2)).
Titulo: Assessment of perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-δ oxides as anodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: To achieve better electrochemical performance, it is necessary to add ceria-supported palladium catalyst for operation with humidified CH4.
Titulo: Assessment of perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-δ oxides as anodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: Anode polarization resistance increases with Sc doping due to a decrease in electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Assessment of perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-δ oxides as anodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: An electrolyte-supported cell with a LSSM-YSZ composite anode delivers peak power densities of 395 and 340 mW cm(-2) at 923 K in humidified (3% H2O) H-2 and CH4, respectively, at a flow rate of 20 mL min(-1).
Titulo: Assessment of perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2ScxMn1-xO3-δ oxides as anodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels
